fields.name: vault_manager
docs: Vault manager ensures that the vault account remains up to date.
Initially, all managers are set to vault manager.

fields.name: reward_manager
docs: Reward manager determines who can harvest rewards,
accumulated in the vault's ATA.

fields.name: fund_manager
docs: Fund manager is responsible for depositing and withdrawing VST
in the vault, which directly affects the vault's TVL.

fields.name: solv_manager
docs: Solv manager operates the vault to interact with the Solv protocol,
expecting to earn yield.

fields.name: vrt_withdrawal_enqueued_amount
docs: request(state == ENQUEUED).vrt_withrawal_requested_amount

fields.name: vrt_withdrawal_processing_amount
docs: request(state == PROCESSING).vrt_withrawal_requested_amount

fields.name: vrt_withdrawal_completed_amount
docs: request(state == COMPLETED).vrt_withrawal_requested_amount

fields.name: one_vrt_as_micro_vst
docs: informative VRT redemption rate.

fields.name: vst_operation_reserved_amount
docs: VST reserved amount for operation - will be deposited to the Solv protocol

fields.name: vst_operation_receivable_amount
docs: VST receivable amount for operation - offsetted by fund manager
## Where does VST receivables come from?
During deposit & withdraw from solv protocol, there is a protocol fee.
It will prevent the NAV loss considering fee as receivable.
Receivables will then be offsetted when fund manager withdraws VST, as a withdrawal fee.

fields.name: vst_withdrawal_locked_amount
docs: VST locked amount for withdrawal - will be locked until withdrawal is completed

fields.name: vst_reserved_amount_to_claim
docs: Ready to claim amount.

fields.name: vst_extra_amount_to_claim
docs: Extra VST amount that exceeded the VST estimated withdrawal amount.

fields.name: vst_deducted_fee_amount
docs: Deducted VST fee amount during withdrawal.

fields.name: vst_receivable_amount_to_claim
docs: Waiting for withdrawal to complete.
Withdrawal fee is not applied yet, so these amount minus fee amount is the exact
amount that will be able to claim when withdrawal is completed.

fields.name: srt_operation_reserved_amount
docs: SRT reserved amount for operation - used to withdraw VST from the solv protocol

fields.name: srt_withdrawal_locked_amount
docs: SRT locked amount for withdrawal - will be sent to the Solv protocol when withdrawal starts

fields.name: one_srt_as_micro_vst
docs: SRT redemption rate being used for vault net asset value appreciation.

fields.name: srt_withdrawal_locked_amount
docs: Locked SRT amount for withdrawal - will be sent to the Solv protocol when withdrawal starts (but field remains unchanged)

fields.name: vst_withdrawal_locked_amount
docs: Locked VST amount for withdrawal - will be locked until withdrawal is completed (but field remains unchanged)

fields.name: vst_withdrawal_total_estimated_amount
docs: Total estimated amount of VST to be withdrawn by this request.
First recorded as `vst_receivable_amount_to_claim` when withdrawal starts,
then after withdrawal completes, the actual VST withdrawn amount is recorded as
`vst_reserved_amount_to_claim` + `vst_extra_amount_to_claim` + `vst_deducted_fee_amount`.
Deducted solv protocol withdrawal fee is added to `vst_deducted_fee_amount`.
```txt
`vst_withdrawal_total_estimated_amount` = `srt_withdrawal_locked_amount` as VST + `vst_withdrawal_locked_amount` + `vst_deducted_fee_amount`

fields.name: one_srt_as_micro_vst
docs: SRT price when requeest is enqueued - will be used for price validation

fields.name: state
docs: 0: enqueued
1: processing
2: completed
